 levels resulting in a nuclear catastrophe comparable in cost to chernobyl it derives generic lessons for industrial structure and regulatory frame for the electric power industry by identifying the two shortcomings of a horizontal coordination mechanism instability under large shocks and the lack of defense in depth the suggested policy response is to harness the power of open interface rule based modularity by creating an independent nuclear safety commission and an independent system operator owning the transmission grid module in japan we propose a transitory price mechanism that can restrain price volatility while providing investment incentives download html+ go to site external http papers ssrn com sol3 papers parent research from crisis to opportunity japan's post 3 11 disaster experience japan studies program project topics investment nuclear power nuclear safety and security japan search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publication news signs of growth in post fukushima japan say stanford experts january 30 2012 japan studies program news publications of interest reducing uncertainty intelligence analysis and national security thomas fingar stanford university press 2011 html+ cover managing pest resistance in fragmented farms an analysis of the risk of bt cotton in china and its zero refuge strategy and beyond scott rozelle fangbin qiao jim wilen jikun huang 2007 pdf+ insuring rural china's health an empirical analysis of china's new collective medical system scott rozelle yuanyuan yan linxiu zhang h holly wang 2006 pdf+ water price policy analysis in china an experimental approach scott rozelle qiuqiong huang jikun huang jinxia wang jun xia 2007 pdf+ cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
